- Experiments starting from January 1, 2023, are considered;
- The cumulative count is calculated for each combination of genotype, chemical, and irrigation method;
- The results are ordered by genotype ID, chemical ID, irrigation ID, and start date.

- "Total plant counts" refer to the sum of plants across all roles involved in the experiment;
- "Experiment duration" is calculated as the difference between the maximum end date and the minimum start date for each experiment;
- "Observers" can have roles such as lead or assistant;
- "Validation results" include the count of validation entries for each parameter and rule;
- "Activity logs" record different activities such as create, update, and delete.

